Unlike earlier work on Higgs production, the present calculation must account for the pseudoscalar nature of j mesons. In particular, if we denote by \Gamma _* the effective fl \Gamma j vertex and in the high-energy limit keep only the transverse polarizations of the virtual photons, the coupling of an j to the coherent nuclear electromagnetic current can be expressed in the form

